npc/hendra: Welcome to what used to be called Sunrise City.
npc/hendra: We don't call it that anymore.
npc/hendra: First, understand what did this. "Judi online" — online gambling. Betting real money on games of pure chance, through apps and websites, any hour of any day.
npc/hendra: It is dressed up as a game. It is not one. It is built so the operator — the house — always profits, and the player, over time, always loses.
npc/hendra: Three years ago, glowing creatures appeared at night. We called them Adbots.
npc/hendra: They didn't attack at first. They just... flashed. Like advertisements. "WIN BIG TONIGHT. FREE CREDITS. GUARANTEED JACKPOT."
npc/hendra: People downloaded the apps they promoted. That's when the Bandits came.
npc/hendra: The Bandits carry slot-machine patterns on their skin. One touch and you can't stop fighting them — just like you can't stop spinning.
npc/hendra: When people had nothing left, She arrived. The Witch. Calling herself a lender.
npc/hendra: "I'll help you win it back," she promised. No one ever did.
npc/hendra: My son, Adit, found one of those apps on a night I was too tired to notice. Six months — that is all it took to gamble away everything I built in twenty years.
npc/hendra: There is no clever machine in this stage yet — nothing dragging you back. Just the creatures, and the truth of what they are.
npc/hendra: Talk to the others here. Learn what online gambling is, how many forms it wears, and how many people it has already swallowed.
npc/hendra: Remember it. Deeper in, the traps get smarter.
